{
  "id": "RAW_4181646f",
  "title": "使用 Gemini CLI 在 GKE 上实现经济高效的大语言模型工作负载",
  "url": "https://cloud.google.com/blog/products/containers-kubernetes/use-gemini-cli-for-cost-effective-llm-workloads-on-gke/",
  "date": "2025-10-17 00:00:00",
  "author": "Shuwen Fang, Anna Pendleton",
  "siteName": "Google Cloud Blog",
  "content": "<html>\n <head></head>\n <body>\n  <section class=\"Wy08Ac nRhiJb-qJTHM-OWXEXe-hJDwNd nRhiJb-DbgRPb-II5mzb-cGMI2b\">\n   <div jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" jscontroller=\"M0Q3Qb\" class=\" \">\n    <p><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Deploying LLM workloads can be complex and costly, often involving a lengthy, multi-step process. To solve this, Google Kubernetes Engine (GKE) offers </span><a href=\"https://cloud.google.com/kubernetes-engine/docs/how-to/machine-learning/inference/inference-quickstart\" track-name=\"inference quickstart\" track-type=\"inline link\" track-metadata-eventdetail=\"cloud.google.com/kubernetes-engine/docs/how-to/machine-learning/inference/inference-quickstart\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;vertical-align:baseline\">Inference Quickstart</span></a><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">.</span></p>\n    <p><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">With Inference Quickstart, you can replace months of manual trial-and-error with out-of-the-box manifests and data-driven insights. Inference Quickstart integrates with the Gemini CLI through native Model Context Protocol (MCP) support to offer tailored recommendations for your LLM workload cost and performance needs. Together, these tools empower you to analyze, select, and deploy your LLMs on GKE in a matter of minutes. Here’s how.&nbsp;</span></p>\n    <h3 class=\"MnozTc-Bz112c MnozTc-Bz112c-OWXEXe-R6PoUb\"><strong style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">1. Select and serve your LLM on GKE via Gemini CLI</strong></h3>\n    <p><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">You can install the </span><a href=\"https://github.com/google-gemini/gemini-cli\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" track-name=\"gemini cli\" track-type=\"inline link\" track-metadata-eventdetail=\"github.com/google-gemini/gemini-cli\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;vertical-align:baseline\">gemini cli</span></a><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"> and </span><a href=\"https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/gke-mcp\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" track-name=\"gke-mcp\" track-type=\"inline link\" track-metadata-eventdetail=\"github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/gke-mcp\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;vertical-align:baseline\">gke-mcp</span></a><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"> server with the following steps:</span></p>\n   </div>\n  </section>\n  <section class=\"nRhiJb-DbgRPb-II5mzb-cGMI2b\">\n   <section>\n    <div class=\"kg99be\" jscontroller=\"vkZm2d\" jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" data-text-to-copy=\"# install Gemini CLI (additional instructions)\nbrew install gemini-cli\n\n# install gke-mcp (additional instructions)\ncurl -sSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/gke-mcp/main/install.sh | bash\n\n# install gke-mcp as Gemini CLI extension\ngke-mcp install gemini-cli\" soy-skip=\"\" ssk=\"4:dXrt\">\n     <div jsaction=\"click:VTVhdd\" class=\"GaRnv\"></div>\n     <div jscontroller=\"M2lJBf\" jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" data-enable-content-editable-input-style=\"false\" data-enable-line-wrapping=\"\" data-read-only=\"\">\n      <div dir=\"ltr\">\n       <textarea jsname=\"bqeLof\" class=\"Fdco1c\" style=\"display: none;\"># install Gemini CLI (additional instructions)\nbrew install gemini-cli\n\n# install gke-mcp (additional instructions)\ncurl -sSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/gke-mcp/main/install.sh | bash\n\n# install gke-mcp as Gemini CLI extension\ngke-mcp install gemini-cli</textarea>\n       <div class=\"CodeMirror cm-s-default CodeMirror-wrap\" translate=\"no\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%;\">\n        <div style=\"overflow:hidden;top:4px;left:4px;width:3px;height:0px;\">\n         <textarea autocorrect=\"off\" autocapitalize=\"off\" spellcheck=\"false\" disabled readonly tabindex=\"0\" style=\"padding:0px;outline:none;bottom:-1em;width:100%;min-height:1em;height:1em;\"></textarea>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"CodeMirror-scroll\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n         <div class=\"CodeMirror-sizer\" style=\"margin-left: 0px; margin-bottom: -15px; border-right-width: 35px; min-height: 400px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px;\">\n          <div style=\"top:0px;\">\n           <div class=\"CodeMirror-lines\" role=\"presentation\">\n            <div role=\"presentation\" style=\"outline:none;\">\n             <div class=\"CodeMirror-measure\">\n              <span><span>​</span>x</span>\n             </div>\n             <div class=\"CodeMirror-cursors\"></div>\n             <div class=\"CodeMirror-code\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"\">\n              <div>\n               <pre class=\" CodeMirror-line \" role=\"presentation\"><span role=\"presentation\" style=\"padding-right: 0.1px;\"># install Gemini CLI (additional instructions)</span></pre>\n              </div>\n              <div>\n               <pre class=\" CodeMirror-line \" role=\"presentation\"><span role=\"presentation\" style=\"padding-right: 0.1px;\">brew install gemini-cli</span></pre>\n              </div>\n              <div>\n               <pre class=\" CodeMirror-line \" role=\"presentation\"><span role=\"presentation\" style=\"padding-right: 0.1px;\"><span cm-text=\"\">​</span></span></pre>\n              </div>\n              <div>\n               <pre class=\" CodeMirror-line \" role=\"presentation\"><span role=\"presentation\" style=\"padding-right: 0.1px;\"># install gke-mcp (additional instructions)</span></pre>\n              </div>\n              <div>\n               <pre class=\" CodeMirror-line \" role=\"presentation\"><span role=\"presentation\" style=\"padding-right: 0.1px;\">curl -sSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/gke-mcp/main/install.sh | bash</span></pre>\n              </div>\n              <div>\n               <pre class=\" CodeMirror-line \" role=\"presentation\"><span role=\"presentation\" style=\"padding-right: 0.1px;\"><span cm-text=\"\">​</span></span></pre>\n              </div>\n              <div>\n               <pre class=\" CodeMirror-line \" role=\"presentation\"><span role=\"presentation\" style=\"padding-right: 0.1px;\"># install gke-mcp as Gemini CLI extension</span></pre>\n              </div>\n              <div>\n               <pre class=\" CodeMirror-line \" role=\"presentation\"><span role=\"presentation\" style=\"padding-right: 0.1px;\">gke-mcp install gemini-cli</span></pre>\n              </div>\n             </div>\n            </div>\n           </div>\n          </div>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"CodeMirror-gutters\" style=\"height: 435px;\"></div>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"nRhiJb-cHYyed nRhiJb-DbgRPb-R6PoUb-ma6Yeb TxA6Xc\"></p>\n   </section>\n  </section>\n  <section class=\"Wy08Ac nRhiJb-qJTHM-OWXEXe-hJDwNd nRhiJb-DbgRPb-II5mzb-cGMI2b\">\n   <div jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" jscontroller=\"M0Q3Qb\" class=\" \">\n    <p><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Here are some example prompts that you can give Gemini CLI to select an LLM workload and generate the manifest needed to deploy the model to a GKE cluster:</span></p>\n   </div>\n  </section>\n  <section class=\"nRhiJb-DbgRPb-II5mzb-cGMI2b\">\n   <section>\n    <div class=\"kg99be\" jscontroller=\"vkZm2d\" jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" data-text-to-copy=\"1. What are the 3 cheapest models available on GKE Inference Quickstart? Can you provide all of the related performance data and accelerators they ran on?\n2. How does this model's performance compare when it was run on different accelerators?\n3. How do I choose between these 2 models?\n4. I’d like to generate a manifest for this model on this accelerator and save it to the current directory.\" soy-skip=\"\" ssk=\"4:dXrt\">\n     <div jsaction=\"click:VTVhdd\" class=\"GaRnv\"></div>\n     <div jscontroller=\"M2lJBf\" jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" data-enable-content-editable-input-style=\"false\" data-enable-line-wrapping=\"\" data-read-only=\"\">\n      <div dir=\"ltr\">\n       <textarea jsname=\"bqeLof\" class=\"Fdco1c\" style=\"display: none;\">1. What are the 3 cheapest models available on GKE Inference Quickstart? Can you provide all of the related performance data and accelerators they ran on?\n2. How does this model's performance compare when it was run on different accelerators?\n3. How do I choose between these 2 models?\n4. I’d like to generate a manifest for this model on this accelerator and save it to the current directory.</textarea>\n       <div class=\"CodeMirror cm-s-default CodeMirror-wrap\" translate=\"no\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%;\">\n        <div style=\"overflow:hidden;top:4px;left:4px;width:3px;height:0px;\">\n         <textarea autocorrect=\"off\" autocapitalize=\"off\" spellcheck=\"false\" disabled readonly tabindex=\"0\" style=\"padding:0px;outline:none;bottom:-1em;width:100%;min-height:1em;height:1em;\"></textarea>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"CodeMirror-scroll\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n         <div class=\"CodeMirror-sizer\" style=\"margin-left: 0px; margin-bottom: -15px; border-right-width: 35px; min-height: 372px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px;\">\n          <div style=\"top:0px;\">\n           <div class=\"CodeMirror-lines\" role=\"presentation\">\n            <div role=\"presentation\" style=\"outline:none;\">\n             <div class=\"CodeMirror-cursors\"></div>\n             <div class=\"CodeMirror-code\" role=\"presentation\">\n              <div>\n               <pre class=\" CodeMirror-line \" role=\"presentation\"><span role=\"presentation\" style=\"padding-right: 0.1px;\">1. What are the 3 cheapest models available on GKE Inference Quickstart? Can you provide all of the related performance data and accelerators they ran on?</span></pre>\n              </div>\n              <div>\n               <pre class=\" CodeMirror-line \" role=\"presentation\"><span role=\"presentation\" style=\"padding-right: 0.1px;\">2. How does this model's performance compare when it was run on different accelerators?</span></pre>\n              </div>\n              <div>\n               <pre class=\" CodeMirror-line \" role=\"presentation\"><span role=\"presentation\" style=\"padding-right: 0.1px;\">3. How do I choose between these 2 models?</span></pre>\n              </div>\n              <div>\n               <pre class=\" CodeMirror-line \" role=\"presentation\"><span role=\"presentation\" style=\"padding-right: 0.1px;\">4. I’d like to generate a manifest for this model on this accelerator and save it to the current directory.</span></pre>\n              </div>\n             </div>\n            </div>\n           </div>\n          </div>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"CodeMirror-gutters\" style=\"height: 407px;\"></div>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"nRhiJb-cHYyed nRhiJb-DbgRPb-R6PoUb-ma6Yeb TxA6Xc\"></p>\n   </section>\n  </section>\n  <section class=\"Wy08Ac nRhiJb-qJTHM-OWXEXe-hJDwNd nRhiJb-DbgRPb-II5mzb-cGMI2b\">\n   <div jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" jscontroller=\"M0Q3Qb\" class=\" \">\n    <p><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">This video below shows an end-to-end example of how you can quickly identify and deploy your optimal LLM workload to a pre-existing GKE cluster via this Gemini CLI setup:</span></p>\n   </div>\n  </section>\n  <section class=\"YNV64d\">\n   <section>\n    <div jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" jscontroller=\"wJu6E\" class=\"nRhiJb-aTv5jf glue-video__preview-container glue-video__preview-container--inline\" data-video-url=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j8AoLxeO_KA\" tabindex=\"0\" role=\"button\">\n     <div class=\"glue-video__preview-container p7j5vb vgZZI glue-video__preview-container--inline\">\n      <picture class=\"nRhiJb-zTg1Jd\">\n       <section class=\"PBkdHd \">\n        <img class=\" glue-video__preview-image\" src=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-cloudblog-publish/images/maxresdefault_FO4rbPT.max-1300x1300.jpg\" alt=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-cloudblog-publish/images/maxresdefault_FO4rbPT.max-1300x1300.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\">\n       </section>\n      </picture>\n      <div class=\"nRhiJb-hEKMR\"></div>\n     </div>\n     <div class=\"glue-video__container nRhiJb-LilHSb-OWXEXe-TzA9Ye vgZZI glue-video--hidden\" data-glue-yt-video-height=\"100%\" data-glue-yt-video-width=\"100%\" tabindex=\"0\" id=\"youtube-player-914361\">\n      <iframe frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" title=\"Use Gemini CLI to deploy more cost effective LLM workloads on GKE\" width=\"100%\" height=\"100%\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/j8AoLxeO_KA?origin=https%3A%2F%2Fcloud.google.com&amp;enablejsapi=1&amp;widgetid=1&amp;forigin=https%3A%2F%2Fcloud.google.com%2Fblog%2Fproducts%2Fcontainers-kubernetes%2Fuse-gemini-cli-for-cost-effective-llm-workloads-on-gke%2F&amp;aoriginsup=1&amp;vf=1\" id=\"widget2\"></iframe>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n   </section>\n  </section>\n  <section class=\"Wy08Ac nRhiJb-qJTHM-OWXEXe-hJDwNd nRhiJb-DbgRPb-II5mzb-cGMI2b\">\n   <div jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" jscontroller=\"M0Q3Qb\" class=\" \">\n    <h3 class=\"MnozTc-Bz112c MnozTc-Bz112c-OWXEXe-ibL1re\"><strong style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">2. Save money while maintaining performance</strong></h3>\n    <p><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Choosing the right hardware for your inference workload means balancing performance and cost. The trade-off is nonlinear. To simplify this complex trade-off, Inference Quickstart provides performance and cost insights across various accelerators, all backed by Google's benchmarks.</span></p>\n    <p><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">For example, as shown in the graph below, minimizing latency for a model like Gemma 3 4b on vLLM dramatically increases cost. This is because achieving ultra-low latency requires sacrificing the efficiency of request batching, which leaves your accelerators underutilized. Request load, model size, architecture, and workload characteristics can all impact which accelerator is optimal for your specific use case.</span></p>\n   </div>\n  </section>\n  <section class=\"QzPuud\">\n   <div>\n    <section>\n     <figure class=\"NEBdNd\">\n      <section class=\"PBkdHd DhGbH\" jscontroller=\"SCGBie\" jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\">\n       <img class=\"JcsBte mZzdH ZOnyjc\" src=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-cloudblog-publish/images/image1_NKTHzu1.max-1000x1000.png\" alt=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/gweb-cloudblog-publish/images/image1_NKTHzu1.max-1000x1000.png\" jsname=\"P3Vluc\" jsaction=\"click:HTIlC\" loading=\"lazy\">\n      </section>\n     </figure>\n    </section>\n   </div>\n  </section>\n  <section class=\"Wy08Ac nRhiJb-qJTHM-OWXEXe-hJDwNd nRhiJb-DbgRPb-II5mzb-cGMI2b\">\n   <div jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" jscontroller=\"M0Q3Qb\" class=\" \">\n    <p><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">To make an informed decision, you can get instant, data-driven recommendations by asking Gemini CLI or using the Inference Quickstart </span><a href=\"https://colab.research.google.com/github/GoogleCloudPlatform/kubernetes-engine-samples/blob/main/ai-ml/notebooks/giq_visualizations.ipynb\" rel=\"opener\" target=\"_blank\" track-name=\"colab notebook\" track-type=\"inline link\" track-metadata-eventdetail=\"colab.research.google.com/github/GoogleCloudPlatform/kubernetes-engine-samples/blob/main/ai-ml/notebooks/giq_visualizations.ipynb\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;vertical-align:baseline\">Colab notebook</span></a><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">.</span></p>\n    <h3 class=\"MnozTc-Bz112c MnozTc-Bz112c-OWXEXe-c5RTEf\"><strong style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">3. Calculate cost per input/output token</strong></h3>\n    <p><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">When you host your own model on a platform like GKE, you are billed for accelerator time, not for each individual token. Inference Quickstart calculates cost per token using the accelerator’s hourly cost and the input/output throughput.</span></p>\n    <p><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">The following formula attributes the total accelerator cost to both input and output tokens:</span></p>\n   </div>\n  </section>\n  <section class=\"nRhiJb-DbgRPb-II5mzb-cGMI2b\">\n   <section>\n    <div class=\"kg99be\" jscontroller=\"vkZm2d\" jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" data-text-to-copy=\"$/output token = Accelerator $/s / (1/4 input tokens/s + output tokens/s)\n\nwhere\n$/input token = ($/output token) / 4\" soy-skip=\"\" ssk=\"4:dXrt\">\n     <div jsaction=\"click:VTVhdd\" class=\"GaRnv\"></div>\n     <div jscontroller=\"M2lJBf\" jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" data-enable-content-editable-input-style=\"false\" data-enable-line-wrapping=\"\" data-read-only=\"\">\n      <div dir=\"ltr\">\n       <textarea jsname=\"bqeLof\" class=\"Fdco1c\" style=\"display: none;\">$/output token = Accelerator $/s / (1/4 input tokens/s + output tokens/s)\n\nwhere\n$/input token = ($/output token) / 4</textarea>\n       <div class=\"CodeMirror cm-s-default CodeMirror-wrap\" translate=\"no\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%;\">\n        <div style=\"overflow:hidden;top:4px;left:4px;width:3px;height:0px;\">\n         <textarea autocorrect=\"off\" autocapitalize=\"off\" spellcheck=\"false\" disabled readonly tabindex=\"0\" style=\"padding:0px;outline:none;bottom:-1em;width:100%;min-height:1em;height:1em;\"></textarea>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"CodeMirror-scroll\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n         <div class=\"CodeMirror-sizer\" style=\"margin-left: 0px; margin-bottom: -15px; border-right-width: 35px; min-height: 148px; padding-right: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px;\">\n          <div style=\"top:0px;\">\n           <div class=\"CodeMirror-lines\" role=\"presentation\">\n            <div role=\"presentation\" style=\"outline:none;\">\n             <div class=\"CodeMirror-measure\">\n              <span><span>​</span>x</span>\n             </div>\n             <div class=\"CodeMirror-cursors\"></div>\n             <div class=\"CodeMirror-code\" role=\"presentation\">\n              <div>\n               <pre class=\" CodeMirror-line \" role=\"presentation\"><span role=\"presentation\" style=\"padding-right: 0.1px;\">$/output token = Accelerator $/s / (1/4 input tokens/s + output tokens/s)</span></pre>\n              </div>\n              <div>\n               <pre class=\" CodeMirror-line \" role=\"presentation\"><span role=\"presentation\" style=\"padding-right: 0.1px;\"><span cm-text=\"\">​</span></span></pre>\n              </div>\n              <div>\n               <pre class=\" CodeMirror-line \" role=\"presentation\"><span role=\"presentation\" style=\"padding-right: 0.1px;\">where</span></pre>\n              </div>\n              <div>\n               <pre class=\" CodeMirror-line \" role=\"presentation\"><span role=\"presentation\" style=\"padding-right: 0.1px;\">$/input token = ($/output token) / 4</span></pre>\n              </div>\n             </div>\n            </div>\n           </div>\n          </div>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"CodeMirror-gutters\" style=\"height: 183px;\"></div>\n        </div>\n       </div>\n      </div>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"nRhiJb-cHYyed nRhiJb-DbgRPb-R6PoUb-ma6Yeb TxA6Xc\"></p>\n   </section>\n  </section>\n  <section class=\"Wy08Ac nRhiJb-qJTHM-OWXEXe-hJDwNd nRhiJb-DbgRPb-II5mzb-cGMI2b\">\n   <div jsaction=\"rcuQ6b:npT2md\" jscontroller=\"M0Q3Qb\" class=\" \">\n    <p><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">This formula assumes an output token costs four times as much as an input token. The reason for this heuristic is that the prefill phase (processing input tokens) is a highly parallel operation, whereas the decode phase (generating output tokens) is a sequential, auto-regressive process. You can ask Gemini CLI to change this ratio for you to fit your workload's expected input/output ratio.</span></p>\n    <p><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">The key to cost-effective LLM inference is to take a data-driven approach. By relying on benchmarks for your workloads and using metrics like cost per token, you can make informed decisions that directly impact your budget and performance.</span></p>\n    <h3 class=\"MnozTc-Bz112c MnozTc-Bz112c-OWXEXe-II5mzb\"><strong style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Next steps</strong></h3>\n    <p><a href=\"https://cloud.google.com/kubernetes-engine/docs/how-to/machine-learning/inference/inference-quickstart#deploy\" track-name=\"gke inference quickstart\" track-type=\"inline link\" track-metadata-eventdetail=\"cloud.google.com/kubernetes-engine/docs/how-to/machine-learning/inference/inference-quickstart\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;vertical-align:baseline\">GKE Inference Quickstart</span></a><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"> goes beyond cost insights and Gemini CLI integration, including optimizations for </span><a href=\"https://cloud.google.com/kubernetes-engine/docs/how-to/machine-learning/inference/inference-quickstart#storage-optimized\" track-name=\"storage\" track-type=\"inline link\" track-metadata-eventdetail=\"cloud.google.com/kubernetes-engine/docs/how-to/machine-learning/inference/inference-quickstart\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;vertical-align:baseline\">storage</span></a><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">, </span><a href=\"https://cloud.google.com/kubernetes-engine/docs/how-to/machine-learning/inference/inference-quickstart#autoscaling-optimized\" track-name=\"autoscaling\" track-type=\"inline link\" track-metadata-eventdetail=\"cloud.google.com/kubernetes-engine/docs/how-to/machine-learning/inference/inference-quickstart\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;vertical-align:baseline\">autoscaling</span></a><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">, and </span><a href=\"https://cloud.google.com/kubernetes-engine/docs/how-to/machine-learning/inference/inference-quickstart#auto-monitoring\" track-name=\"observability\" track-type=\"inline link\" track-metadata-eventdetail=\"cloud.google.com/kubernetes-engine/docs/how-to/machine-learning/inference/inference-quickstart\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;vertical-align:baseline\">observability</span></a><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">. Run your LLM workloads today with GKE Inference Quickstart to see how it can expedite and optimize your LLMs on GKE.</span></p>\n   </div>\n  </section>\n </body>\n</html>",
  "aiSummary": "本文详细介绍了 Google 的 Gemini CLI 和 GKE 推理快速启动如何通过提供数据驱动的建议和清单生成，简化 GKE 上经济高效的大语言模型部署。",
  "oneSentenceSummary": "本文详细介绍了 Google 的 Gemini CLI 和 GKE 推理快速启动如何通过提供数据驱动的建议和清单生成，简化 GKE 上经济高效的大语言模型部署。",
  "summary": "本文介绍了 Google Kubernetes Engine (GKE) 的推理快速启动，该解决方案旨在简化和优化大语言模型 (LLM) 工作负载的部署。它重点介绍了推理快速启动与 Gemini CLI 的集成，利用模型上下文协议 (MCP)，根据数据驱动的分析结果，为平衡成本和性能提供建议。文章详细介绍了用户如何安装 Gemini CLI 和 `gke-mcp`，以查询最佳大语言模型配置，比较各种加速器上的模型性能，并为 GKE 生成部署清单。它强调了理解性能（例如，延迟）和成本之间的非线性权衡的重要性，提供了来自 Google 基准测试的见解。此外，它还解释了推理快速启动如何计算每个输入/输出 token 的成本，为预算提供了一个实用的指标，并允许用户调整输入/输出 token 成本比率。总体而言，文章提倡采用数据驱动的方法，以实现 GKE 上经济高效的大语言模型推理。此外，GKE 推理快速入门还提供了存储、自动扩缩容和可观测性等方面的优化。",
  "mainPoints": [
    {
      "point": "Gemini CLI 与 GKE 推理快速入门相结合，简化了大语言模型的部署和选择流程。",
      "explanation": "它提供了一个简化的流程来查询、比较和生成 GKE 上大语言模型的部署清单，从而大大减少了开发人员的手动工作和时间。"
    },
    {
      "point": "数据驱动的见解对于平衡 GKE 上的大语言模型性能和成本至关重要。",
      "explanation": "推理快速启动提供了跨各种加速器的基准测试数据，使用户能够做出明智的决策，以优化硬件利用率并避免特定延迟要求的不必要成本。"
    },
